                android:text="Prepare the Broth:

In a large pot, combine the chicken pieces, onion, garlic, ginger, lemongrass (if using), fish sauce, salt, and pepper.

Add enough water to cover the chicken and bring it to a boil. Skim off any impurities that rise to the surface.

Once boiling, lower the heat to a simmer and let it cook until the chicken is tender, usually about 30-40 minutes.

Remove the chicken from the broth and shred the meat. Set aside.

Prepare the Noodles:

Cook the egg noodles according to the package instructions. Drain and set aside.
Assemble Chicken Mami:

In serving bowls, place a portion of cooked egg noodles.

Top the noodles with shredded chicken, sliced hard-boiled eggs, chopped green onions, and fried garlic. You can also add fried tofu or pork wontons if desired.

Ladle the hot chicken broth over the noodles and toppings.

Garnish with fresh cilantro leaves if using.

Serve hot and enjoy!"
